<paragraph id="B87B36C7FF81672E00A424F1FB2FFE50" blockId="53.[151,1154,426,482]" box="[151,1154,458,482]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF81672E00A424F1FE80FE53" bold="true" box="[151,301,458,482]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<typeStatus id="677F8865FF81672E00A424F1FF62FE53" box="[151,207,458,482]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Type</typeStatus>
species:
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF81672E010024F1FDF4FE50" authority="Kondo" authorityName="Kondo" box="[307,601,458,481]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Intecticoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF81672E010024F1FDA7FE50" box="[307,522,458,481]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Intecticoccus viridis</emphasis>
Kondo
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF81672E025A24F1FDD3FE50" box="[617,638,458,481]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">in</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="DC554B36FF81672E02B624F1FB8BFE50" author="Kondo, T. &amp; Hardy, N. &amp; Cook, L. &amp; Gullan, P." box="[645,1062,458,481]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="19 - 36" refId="ref50582" refString="Kondo, T., Hardy, N., Cook, L. &amp; Gullan, P. (2006) Description of two new genera and species of Eriococcidae (Hemiptera: Coccoidea) from southern South America. Zootaxa, 1349, 19 - 36." type="journal article" year="2006">Kondo, Hardy, Cook and Gullan, 2006</bibRefCitation>
): 26–29.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B87B36C7FF81672E00A42734FD1DFCCB" blockId="53.[151,1436,527,1151]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF81672E00A42734FD9CFD98" bold="true" box="[151,561,527,553]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Generic diagnosis. Adult female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="20FF2A42FF81672E0270272BFD33FD9B" box="[579,670,528,554]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="54.[151,257,1788,1812]" captionTargetBox="[249,1341,284,1760]" captionTargetId="figure-154@54.[220,1367,263,1785]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURE 26. Intecticoccus viridis Kondo. Adult female, where A = dorsal setae; B = dorsal microtubular duct; D = dorsal derm, showing areolations; G = dorsal view of anal lobe; H = side view of anal plate plus anal ring; J1, J2 = ventral setae; K = ventral microducts; P = anterior spiracle; Q = labium; V = antenna; W = metathoracic leg, and X = coxa of metathoracic leg. And where dls = dorsolateral lobe seta; dms = dorsomedial lobe seta; das = dorsoapical lobe seta; cs = caudal seta; vls = ventral lobe seta, and sas = suranal seta (modified after Kondo et al., 2006)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5313415" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5313415/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). In life, covered by thin layer of glassy wax, not producing an ovisac; eggs laid in concavity beneath female. Adult female with sclerotised anal lobes variable in shaped, protruding posteriorly. 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF81672E01F62761FD9FFDC2" box="[453,562,602,627]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Dorsum.</emphasis>
Setae short, slightly spinose, of 1 size. Macrotubular ducts absent. Microtubular ducts with longitudinal division. Loculate pores absent. 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF81672E03E027BBFB9FFD28" box="[979,1074,640,665]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Margin.</emphasis>
Not demarcated. 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF81672E053627BBFAF5FD28" box="[1285,1368,640,665]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Venter.</emphasis>
Setae relatively small, slightly spinose or hairlike, most abundant medially, uncommon elsewhere; suranal seta present on sclerotised extension of anal lobes. Macrotubular ducts absent. Microducts present between antennae and in row near anterior spiracles. Loculate pores primarily quinquelocular. Cruciform pores absent. Antennae 6 segmented. Frontal lobes and antennal tubercles absent. Labium 3 segmented; basal segment with 2 pairs of setae. Metathoracic legs with translucent pores on coxa. Claw digitules similar; claw without denticle. Vulva present between VII and VIII.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B87B36C7FF81672E00F526BEFDFAFC2E" blockId="53.[151,1436,527,1151]" box="[198,599,901,927]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
Known only from 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF81672E01AC26BEFDFFFC2E" authorityName="Kuprianova" authorityYear="1962" box="[415,594,901,927]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nothofagaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Nothofagaceae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F0DE654CFF81672E00F52691FAC8FBCF" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="B87B36C7FF81672E00F52691FAC8FBCF" blockId="53.[151,1436,527,1151]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF81672E00F52691FEE6FC75" bold="true" box="[198,331,938,964]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Comment:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF81672E01672691FE42FC72" authorityName="Kondo" authorityYear="2006" box="[340,495,938,963]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Intecticoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF81672E01672691FE42FC72" box="[340,495,938,963]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Intecticoccus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a monotypic genus known only from 
<collectingCountry id="C0D37657FF81672E03E02691FBBFFC75" box="[979,1042,938,964]" name="Chile" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Chile</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="C0D37657FF81672E047D2691FB6BFC75" box="[1102,1222,938,964]" name="Argentina" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Argentina</collectingCountry>
. For a description of the adult female of 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF81672E01AC26EBFDA9FC58" box="[415,516,976,1001]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Intecticoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF81672E01AC26EBFDA9FC58" box="[415,516,976,1001]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">I. viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, see 
<bibRefCitation id="DC554B36FF81672E027226EBFC8EFC5B" author="Kondo, T. &amp; Hardy, N. &amp; Cook, L. &amp; Gullan, P." box="[577,803,976,1002]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="19 - 36" refId="ref50582" refString="Kondo, T., Hardy, N., Cook, L. &amp; Gullan, P. (2006) Description of two new genera and species of Eriococcidae (Hemiptera: Coccoidea) from southern South America. Zootaxa, 1349, 19 - 36." type="journal article" year="2006">
Kondo 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF81672E02AA26EBFD63FC58" box="[665,718,976,1001]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">et al</emphasis>
., 2006
</bibRefCitation>
. Kondo 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF81672E03B426EBFC16FC58" box="[903,955,976,1001]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">et al</emphasis>
. state that 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF81672E040E26EBFB0CFC58" box="[1085,1185,976,1001]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Intecticoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF81672E040E26EBFB0CFC58" box="[1085,1185,976,1001]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">I. viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other species of eriococcids in having the following combination of characters: (i) in life, with bare dorsum, not covered in a felted sac; (ii) very small dorsal and marginal setae, each 3–7 µm long; (iii) claws without a denticle; and (iv) absence of cruciform pores. It shows some similarities to 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF81672E0495217BFEDEFBCE" authority="Miller &amp; Gonzalez" authorityName="Miller &amp; Gonzalez" authorityYear="1975" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Icelococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="charlini">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF81672E0495217BFA31FBE8" box="[1190,1436,1088,1113]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Icelococcus charlini</emphasis>
Miller &amp; González
</taxonomicName>
and to 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF81672E01F8215EFC12FBCE" authority="Hodgson &amp; Miller. For" authorityName="Hodgson &amp; Miller. For" box="[459,959,1125,1151]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Chilechiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lynnae">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF81672E01F8215EFD04FBCF" box="[459,681,1125,1150]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Chilechiton lynnae</emphasis>
Hodgson &amp; Miller. For
</taxonomicName>
differences, see 
<bibRefCitation id="DC554B36FF81672E04B0215EFAF3FBCE" author="Kondo, T. &amp; Hardy, N. &amp; Cook, L. &amp; Gullan, P." box="[1155,1374,1125,1151]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="19 - 36" refId="ref50582" refString="Kondo, T., Hardy, N., Cook, L. &amp; Gullan, P. (2006) Description of two new genera and species of Eriococcidae (Hemiptera: Coccoidea) from southern South America. Zootaxa, 1349, 19 - 36." type="journal article" year="2006">
Kondo 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF81672E04E9215EFAA3FBCF" box="[1242,1294,1125,1150]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">et al</emphasis>
., 2006
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
